[[File:7thAve50thSt.jpg|thumb]]向南看]]

'''第七大道'''（'''Seventh Avenue'''/'''Adam Clayton Powell Jr. Boulevard'''）是美国[[纽约市|纽约市]][[曼哈顿|曼哈顿]]西部的一条干道，西侧与之平行的是[[第八大道|第八大道]]以及中央公园西、Hudson街，东侧与之平行的是[[第六大道|第六大道]]以及Lenox大道。<!-- It carries traffic downtown (southbound) south of [[中央公园|中央公园]] but both ways north of it. -->

第七大道始于[[西村_(曼哈顿)|西村]]的Clarkson街，在那里Varick街变成了第七大道。从[[59街|59街]]到[[110街|110街]]，第七大道被中央公园所阻断。公园以北，<!-- road runs in both directions through [[Harlem|Harlem]], where the road is called '''Adam Clayton Powell Jr. Boulevard'''. The road continues across [[Harlem_River|Harlem River]] via [[Macombs_Dam_Bridge|Macombs Dam Bridge]], where it becomes [[Jerome_Avenue_(Bronx)|Jerome Avenue]] upon reaching [[the_Bronx|the Bronx]]. -->

<!-- Running through [[Garment_District,_Manhattan|Garment District]] (which stretches 从[[12大道|12大道]]到[[第五大道|第五大道]]和[[34街|34街]]到39街，it is referred to as '''Fashion Avenue''' due to its role as a center of the garment and [[fashion|fashion]] industry and the famed [[fashion_design|fashion design]]ers who established New York as a world fashion capital. The first, temporary signs designating the section of Seventh Avenue as "Fashion Avenue" were dual-posted in 1972, with permanent signs added over the ensuing years.<ref>"Everybody -- Well, Almost -- Attended A Mammoth Party on 'Fashion Ave.'", ''[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]'', [[June_8|June 8]], [[1972|1972]]. p. 58.</ref> -->

第七大道另一个著名的地点就是与[[百老汇|百老汇]]及[[42街|42街]]交汇处的[[时报广场|时报广场]]。<!-- [[Carnegie_Hall|Carnegie Hall]], [[Madison_Square_Garden|Madison Square Garden]] and [[Pennsylvania_Station_(New_York_City)|Penn Station]],[[Fashion_Institute_of_Technology|Fashion Institute of Technology]], and [[James_J._Walker_Park|James J. Walker Park]] are some of the notable destinations that reside along 第七大道. -->

[[安盛中心|安盛中心]]（AXA Center，原Equitable Tower)，位于第七大道787号，是一座高229米（752英尺）的摩天大楼，建于1986年，[[安盛保险|安盛集团]]（AXA）设此。目前底层的承租人有[[BNP_Paribas|BNP Paribas]]、Sidley Austin LLP和[[花旗银行|花旗银行]]，穿过街道，西北面是[[第七大道810号|第七大道810号]]（810 Seventh Avenue），北面和西面是2座喜来登酒店。

<!-- The street is mentioned in [[Simon_and_Garfunkel|Simon and Garfunkel]] song ''[[The_Boxer|The Boxer]],'' in which the protagonist mentions receiving "come-ons from the [[prostitution|whores]] on Seventh Avenue." It is also mentioned in [[Dashiell_Hammett|Dashiell Hammett]]'s ''[[The_Maltese_Falcon|The Maltese Falcon]]'', when detective Sam Spade tells the gunman Wilmer that his telling him to "shove off" "would go over big back on Seventh Avenue. But you're not in Romeville now. You're in my burg." -->

